==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ɡɹʌb/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌb|-ʌb]]

===Noun===
'''grub''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]''; ''plural'' '''[[grubs]]''')

#(''[[countable]]'') an [[immature]] [[stage]] in the [[life cycle]] of an [[insect]]; a [[larva]].
#(''[[uncountable]]'') (''slang'') food.

====Synonyms====
*(''immature insect''): [[larva]]
*(''slang: food''): [[nosh]], [[tucker]]

====Translations====
'''immature insect'''
*French: larve
*German: [[Wurm]] {{m}}
*Italian: [[bruco]] {{m}}
''See [[larva]]''

'''slang: food'''
{{top}}
*French: [[bouffe]] {{f}}
{{mid}}
*Romanian: [[larva]] {{f}}
*Russian: [[харчи]] (χarčí) ''m pl''
*Swedish: [[käk]] {{n}}
{{bottom}}

===Verb===
'''grub'''
# to [[scavenge]] or in some way [[scrounge]], typically for food.

====Related terms====
*[[grubby]]
*[[witchetty grub]]

